{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Dw2TWTgkifc4V6fxt8WKAQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the setup. There are two Ingress resources for `rate.example.com`:\n1. `rate-api` - handles `/api` path\n2. `rate-health` - handles `/health` path\n\nNeither has any rate limiting annotations. I need to:\n1. Add rate limiting to the `rate-api` ingress with 1 QPS limit\n2. Make rate-limited responses return HTTP 429 (nginx-ingress default is 503, so I need to set the status code)\n3. Leave `rate-health` unchanged\n\nThe nginx ingress controller annotations for rate limiting are:\n- `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-rps` for requests per second\n- `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-connections` for max concurrent connections\n- `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-burst-multiplier` for burst allowance\n\nTo return 429 instead of 503, I need `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-status-code` set to \"429\", though this annotation's availability depends on the nginx-ingress version being used.\n\nFor the rate-api ingress, I'd set a 1 QPS limit with the default burst of 5, but I need to think through what happens when traffic exceeds that threshold. So I'm thinking through the nginx leaky bucket algorithm more carefully. With a burst multiplier of 1, the burst capacity equals the rate limit itself, making it much stricter—at 2 QPS against a 1 QPS limit, roughly every other request would get rejected. Let me adjust the burst multiplier to enforce this tighter constraint. With burst=1, the pattern becomes much more restrictive—roughly alternating between passes and rejections, giving us about 5 passes and 5 failures out of 10 requests, which should satisfy the \"at least 4 rejected\" requirement.\n\nI'll configure the ingress with a 1 RPS limit and burst multiplier of 1, but I need to verify whether the `limit-status-code` annotation is actually supported in this version of nginx-ingress before committing to it.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5061,"cache_read_input_tokens":30600,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5061},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ae1eda0e-88ea-476c-ad9d-4f04b0c7aaad","uuid":"36a29e6b-d1ad-4c78-ab31-734ab77325ee","request_id":"req_011CcLvqXNuK3YjR7JudUxfG"}
